#!/usr/local/bin/perl -d

# run oracdr with perl debugging turned on

$oracdir = $ENV{ORAC_DIR}."/bin";
require "$oracdir/oracdr";


=head1 NAME

oracdr_db - run oracdr with perl debugging turned on

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  oracdr_db

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Run ORAC-DR with perl debugging turned on.
A simple perl wrapper using the C<-d> switch and C<require>.

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<oracdr>

